description: For sale: $199,900. Own a beautiful home in one of Duluth's most sought after neighborhoods.  This is a classic Observation Hill, turn of the century, Victorian style home with 11 ft ceilings and BIG incredible panoramic views! Check out the photos...  Spectacular unobstructed views of Lake Superior, lift bridge, Park Point, Harbor, Wisconsin and much of the city, especially from the master bedroom.   The home features hardwood floors, open floor plan, pocket doors between Living Room and Dining Room, and Large Open Kitchen.  Short walk/ride to Enger Tower, Twin Ponds, Lake Superior Hiking Trail, Enger Golf Course, and the Duluth Traverse mountain biking trail.

For sale: $109,900. Available now! Scenic views of Duluth Aerial Lift Bridge and Lake Superior from living room, the master bedroom, and your front steps, where there's room for a small outdoor table and chairs! Large deck in back with views of Lake Superior and Duluth Harbor, great place for BBQs, entertaining, dining, and relaxing. 

This is near-downtown town Duluth living at its best, plus low-down owner financing is available with as little as $5000 down. This comfy and solid three bedroom, two bath, two story efficient home is well-built with thick stone walls and many modern updates. 

Not yet qualified for a morgage, or would like to get moved in quicker than a bank could close? A private Seller financing  (no bank loan or mortgage needed!) is possible with as little as $5000 down with approved application. Spacious 1454 square feet plus unfinished, dry basement. Nice hardwood floors in living room and dining room, new floors in kitchen and bath. Brand new carpet in the three upstairs bedrooms halls, and stairs, where there's also a full bath. Half bath on main floor for convenience as well. Home is in a quiet, tidy neighborhood, with a park and playground nearby, and wonderful views of the lake and harbor, as well as Bayfront Park, from which music will waft up on summer evenings. Full, unfinished basement has lots of storage room. 

Newer high efficiency natural gas furnace, new plumbing, roof, and a classic clawfoot tub and shower. Walls are thick, so it's quiet and surprisingly affordable to heat; highest gas heat bill last 3 winters was under $170. This is Fee Simple, "owned land," meaning you own the land under this townhouse so there are NO pesky HOA or condo fees. 

A DTA bus stop (#14) is on the corner, barely 50 feet from your front door. It's the green corner unit in the photo, closest to the photographer. With 10% down, payments would be in $800 range including taxes and insurance, cheaper than rent! Perfect for a biking or bus or Uber/Lyfting owner, close to downtown as well as West Duluth, Denfeld, Lincoln Park, etc. No garage, but there's plenty of close on-street parking within steps of your door. When you reply please include "Duluth Home" or local reference in your subject line so I know you're real, and include your name and phone number, so I can contact you about a showing. Serious inquiries from serious lookers/buyers only with down payment cash and at least $2700/mo provable income or pre-qualified mortgage.

Each of 3 units has 2 bedrooms, 1 bath, in unit laundry hook-ups, 1 car detached garage, and deck.  Fully equipped kitchen..  Seasonal Lake view!   Association fees include water and sewer, house electric meter, garbage, snow removal, and lawn care.

description: Recently sold: $127,900. Cute, clean, and updated traditional in Upper Lincoln Park. description: Recently sold: $190,000. 507-511 N Lake Ave is a great investment opportunity! description: Recently sold: $300,000. Stunning Lake Superior & City Light Views that sweep the horizon from so many levels and rooms. The Homeowner thought of everything during at time of new construction including a floor plan that captures the views from almost every room.Beautifully renovated home with Granite, fixture upgrades, kitchen cabinets, appliances, flooring and new roof. 3 Bathrooms, one on every level,plus a Sauna w/ shower. Open Loft with built-in library provides opportunity for 3 Spacious Bedrooms that accommodate king size beds plus furniture. Master bedroom with large walk in closet and walk through Master Bathroom and private deck overlooking the City of Duluth, Lake and Bay views that span into Wisconsin. Conveniently located main floor laundry. The lower level offers additional space for a den or fitness room. The attached garage has plenty of space for your tools and vehicles. Spacious foyer for all of your guests, boots, coats and gear. A custom, spacious and open floor plan creates so many wonderful living space opportunities. This is a one owner, smoke free-pet free well loved home and first time on the market! Perfect walking & biking distance to downtown employment, entertainment and the 4th of July fireworks display is viewed from your home. The Sellers want to share their home with you, come on in and enjoy Three Decks and a 3-Season Sun Porch that creates wonderful opportunities for hosting get-togethers and beautiful family memories. The show over the city and Lake Superior change every evening; certainly quality memories are made here.

description: Recently sold: $212,500. 926 W 5th St is a beautiful 3 bed, 2 1/2 bath home with a VIEW! Incredible views of Lake Superior, the Bay, and Park Point. Big master bedroom upstairs includes a walk-in closet, master bath with jetted tub, and a sitting area with lake views - a perfect place to enjoy your morning coffee! Outside is a big front yard with a creek next door (city land), lots of perennials, a back deck (great spot for grilling!), and a 2 car tuckunder garage(18x28) with extra off-street parking. Come take a look today!

Call for details and a private showing... Asking 249,900 and accepting offers

description: Recently sold: $105,000. Traditional Observation Hill duplex. 2 bed/1bath unit?s with full bath, large living room, separate dining room, large kitchen., porches, semi views, off street parking, new boiler, and on demand hot water,  new roof May, 2018.  Free washer and dryer.

Recently sold: $125,000. This house is just off the highway, so it's in a great location for commuting anywhere within the city fast. The best part is, you'd never know it sitting out in the backyard. Tree cover and grape vines surround the fenced in backyard, and I don't ever notice any traffic noise.
The house has a full walkout basement, that is partially finished with a large recreation room and a 3/4 bathroom. The main floor has one bedroom, a full bathroom, the kitchen, dining, and living room. The second floor has two more bedrooms, as well as a small room that I use for an office, but was previously used as a nursery. There is also plenty of storage space with each bedroom containing a large closet, as well as other closets throughout the house.
The main floor and second floor have the original maple floors. This house does have a lot of updates: I believe the plumbing, electrical system, windows and roof were all updated within the last 10 years. It has steel siding, and all of the soffit, facia, and trim are aluminum wrapped, with seamless gutters. The new furnace was installed 3 years ago and is a 98% efficiency natural gas furnace.

I contract painting, and work in the flooring business, so I am more than willing to work a fresh paint job and possibly some new flooring into the sales agreement.

Sit at your kitchen table & enjoy the back gardens and private deck. 3 bedrooms up, (2 w/ bay views) bathroom. description: Recently sold: $191,151. If you're looking for single-level living you might consider this home. Most of the living space is on the main level, with laundry in the lower level which is mostly finished--and finished nicely! Charming original hardwood floors comingle with today's quality finishes to create a home that is so versatile as well as sturdy and reliable. 2 BRs and a full bath on the main floor, with an egressed BR on the walk-out lower level along with a 3/4 bath, a sauna and an office/work room. Furnace, water heater, windows & doors, electrical all have been updated recently. The back yard is fully fenced and includes a deck and some garden areas, if you like that. The 2-car garage is oversized and recently an extra paved parking pad was put in place so that you can store your RV or extra wheels. 25th Ave is a dead-end so you'll not have lots of traffic going by, yet you're so conveniently located! Just minutes to the mall area or scoot down the hill to West Duluth and the interstate.
